Cell["\<\
The characteristic property of quantum information that distinguishes it from \
classical information is that it can take an arbitrary continuous \
superposition of logical states. Naturally, errors in quantum information \
form a continuum given that any slightest deviation in the superposition \
results in an error. At first glance, it may cast immense difficulties even \
in detecting errors. Ironically, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]continuous\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] quantum information bears a striking difference from \
the information stored in classical analog systems, and errors in the quantum \
information can be \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]discretized\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \
so to speak. In this section, we will show this in two stages. We first \
discuss the conditions for the errors to be corrected. We then proceed to \
show that correcting merely a discrete set of errors suffices to correct the \
continuum of errors in quantum information. These form a basic theory of \
quantum error-correction codes.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->205711485,ExpressionUUID->"15eeaa87-8246-4e28-bb1c-3bff54f21650"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "See also Section 6.2 of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["Quantum Workbook (2022)"]], 
    "https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-91214-7"},
   "WebLink",
   BaseStyle->{"TechNoteText"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "310c4fec-92d1-4c76-9d39-28fae7a269e1"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1308734266,ExpressionUUID->"b36856cf-71cb-49e1-baf8-4ce32de05b7e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Quantum Error-Correction Conditions", "TechNoteSection",
 CellID->1509640923,ExpressionUUID->"489adbd5-0b72-43e6-bc6e-045b6fc08dfa"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We first present a set of simple yet general tests that allow us to \
determine whether a quantum code protects against a certain class of quantum \
noise. Consider a quantum code associated with code space ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[ScriptCapitalV]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cbe1eaff-8a0f-4080-9810-178836e74552"],
 ". We describe the quantum noise causing errors with a quantum operation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4e0a060e-54bf-4741-979e-0afbe4d7e902"],
 " specified by Kraus elements ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"{", 
    SubscriptBox["E", "\[Mu]"], "}"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "eb5be6f1-9fe2-4c59-82ca-cb768dd3bcf8"],
 ". Then, the ",
 StyleBox["quantum error-correction conditions",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " (also known as ",
 StyleBox["Knill",
  IgnoreSpellCheck->True,
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox["-",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox["Laflamme",
  IgnoreSpellCheck->True,
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[" criteria",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ") can be written in a compact way as follows: there exists an \
error-correction or recovery operation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[ScriptCapitalR]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9b8d6da5-e69d-4627-81cb-5630fe6f4745"],
 " that corrects ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[ScriptCapitalE]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d377d6ce-dae7-40e7-8c5a-d08dad452e82"],
 " on ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[ScriptCapitalV]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f3f19434-0f2e-4a6e-964d-869e7feac620"],
 " if and only if every pair of the Kraus elements satisfies"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->15703556,ExpressionUUID->"3b2f58b4-ef38-4e90-b17b-37996a92e2b5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"P", " ", 
     SubsuperscriptBox["E", "\[Mu]", "\[Dagger]"], 
     SubscriptBox["E", "\[Nu]"], "P"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["A", 
      RowBox[{"\[Mu]", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "\[Nu]"}]], "P"}]}], 
   TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"92667964-081c-4fb2-b3fe-93d11998a856"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1936660758,ExpressionUUID->"c1292311-3c5f-4932-9a70-50dc23891813"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "for a certain Hermitian matrix ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["A", "\[Mu]\[Nu]"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "19ada33b-f485-4330-8951-af431e671121"],
 " and all \[Mu] and \[Nu], where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["P", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7c07a187-97b0-411e-841f-35e6de8d1fc0"],
 " is the projector onto code space ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[ScriptCapitalV]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "446627a2-6afe-4f0d-87eb-c05ace7258cc"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->47722127,ExpressionUUID->"b5f628d6-aba2-4e77-bea1-a70246aadb7d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tOne can understand the meaning of the above condition by considering \
specific code words ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     OverscriptBox["x", "_"]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "83d47809-d6d1-43b5-a6ce-7cd8730badb2"],
 "  encoding ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["k", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ae15cfa1-504b-4e77-9fcb-0abe7e26e27b"],
 "-qubit computational basis states ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"x"},
     "Ket"], "\[Congruent]", 
    TemplateBox[{
      RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["x", "1"], 
        SubscriptBox["x", "2"], "\[CenterEllipsis]", " ", 
        SubscriptBox["x", "k"]}]},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "438bb6a8-a259-4988-99d7-590f3633a2ae"],
 " in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "411e767f-415a-4dbf-913b-29990007455f"],
 " qubits. For any two ",
 StyleBox["distinct",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " code words ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     OverscriptBox["x", "_"]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "455a383f-8b9c-4188-99cf-ed3aca10be17"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     OverscriptBox["y", "_"]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c90729e2-306f-482a-bb77-0d23577bb82c"],
 ", the above condition implies that"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1054388158,ExpressionUUID->"dc86bd18-8691-486c-9052-29c0e2905965"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{
       OverscriptBox["x", "_"]},
      "Bra"], 
     SubsuperscriptBox["E", "\[Mu]", "\[Dagger]"], 
     SubscriptBox["E", "\[Nu]"], 
     TemplateBox[{
       OverscriptBox["y", "_"]},
      "Ket"]}], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c99efdc1-cccc-4439-9c11-eb0955ca84dc"]
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->66716462,ExpressionUUID->"4a4340a8-9b4a-43fd-af97-046f2d05ac80"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "regardless of \[Mu] and \[Nu]. This means that corrupted code words ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["E", "\[Mu]"], 
    TemplateBox[{
      OverscriptBox["x", "_"]},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "343d9e0e-7647-47bc-893a-26612d793865"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["E", "\[Nu]"], 
    TemplateBox[{
      OverscriptBox["y", "_"]},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c779aa94-f7a4-4976-8fbd-4468388e0db1"],
 " must remain orthogonal to each other. This is natural since only \
orthogonal states can be discriminated with certainty in quantum mechanics. \
The above condition also implies that the expectation value of given error \
operators,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->317113100,ExpressionUUID->"b1c6fc5b-7c6d-46eb-858d-ecc7af8965ee"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     TemplateBox[{
       OverscriptBox["x", "_"]},
      "Bra"], 
     SubsuperscriptBox["E", "\[Mu]", "\[Dagger]"], 
     SubscriptBox["E", "\[Nu]"], 
     TemplateBox[{
       OverscriptBox["x", "_"]},
      "Ket"]}], "=", 
    SubscriptBox["A", 
     RowBox[{"\[Mu]", "\[VeryThinSpace]", "\[Nu]"}]]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"46038923-1e51-4f76-80ce-26fc31559c0e"],
 " ,"
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1812943493,ExpressionUUID->"0cfb0fe6-292c-4892-82a1-036fb7a693c2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "must be all the same regardless of code words ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     OverscriptBox["x", "_"]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "43c81904-b9f5-4c83-ad6c-1f15e697d95e"],
 ". This means that no error can reveal any information in encoded states."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1643303215,ExpressionUUID->"c62ec2d6-114d-4155-9d36-c0ca2495352a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\tA proof is referred to Section 6.2 of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["Quantum Workbook (2022)"]], 
    "https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-91214-7"},
   "WebLink",
   BaseStyle->{"TechNoteText"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "57786579-97a8-473f-bfd6-c11588a0fec9"],
 "."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1525705079,ExpressionUUID->"d1dd76ca-387a-46ec-b2b8-630b23483da6"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Demonstration", "Subsection",
 CellID->694240628,ExpressionUUID->"f8645a5d-1743-41df-b5b2-800631827492"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<QuantumMob`Q3`\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[10]:=",
 CellID->822413959,ExpressionUUID->"50fd114c-7f17-4460-b24b-a9543dd4eef1"],

Cell["\<\
As an example , let us apply the quantum error-correction conditions to Shor\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s bit-flip code.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->259705806,ExpressionUUID->"e392d485-477d-49c7-b674-24256be8e9f4"],

Cell["Consider a quantum register of three qubits.", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->2141972478,ExpressionUUID->"de179934-d0bf-4134-8a9f-e664469e5fc9"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"$n", "=", "3"}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"Let", "[", 
  RowBox[{"Qubit", ",", "S"}], "]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"SS", "=", 
  RowBox[{"S", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Range", "@", "$n"}], ",", "$"}], "]"}]}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[11]:=",
 CellID->1033400973,ExpressionUUID->"185c410b-61c9-443c-9e09-9449f07d8c86"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   InterpretationBox[
    SubscriptBox["S", 
     TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", "1"},
      "RowWithSeparators"]],
    $CellContext`S[1, Q3`$]], ",", 
   InterpretationBox[
    SubscriptBox["S", 
     TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", "2"},
      "RowWithSeparators"]],
    $CellContext`S[2, Q3`$]], ",", 
   InterpretationBox[
    SubscriptBox["S", 
     TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", "3"},
      "RowWithSeparators"]],
    $CellContext`S[3, Q3`$]]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[13]=",
 CellID->110450584,ExpressionUUID->"233cabd7-947a-4503-887c-e591b899fd02"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["Set the code words, i.e., the logical basis states.", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->122986822,ExpressionUUID->"e52ccd1e-61e0-45e5-98ea-5cbf892a99a8"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"lbs", "=", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Ket", "[", 
     RowBox[{"SS", "->", "0"}], "]"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"Ket", "[", 
     RowBox[{"SS", "->", "1"}], "]"}]}], "}"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[14]:=",
 CellID->426784164,ExpressionUUID->"648fde58-e105-444c-94f0-6df724e35111"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   InterpretationBox[
    TemplateBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"\[VeryThinSpace]", "\"\[VeryThinSpace]\"", 
        SubscriptBox["0", 
         TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", 
           InterpretationBox[
            SubscriptBox["S", 
             TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", "1"}, "RowWithSeparators"]], 
            $CellContext`S[1, Q3`$]]}, "RowWithSeparators"]], 
        SubscriptBox["0", 
         TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", 
           InterpretationBox[
            SubscriptBox["S", 
             TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", "2"}, "RowWithSeparators"]], 
            $CellContext`S[2, Q3`$]]}, "RowWithSeparators"]], 
        SubscriptBox["0", 
         TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", 
           InterpretationBox[
            SubscriptBox["S", 
             TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", "3"}, "RowWithSeparators"]], 
            $CellContext`S[3, Q3`$]]}, "RowWithSeparators"]]}, 
       "RowWithSeparators"]},
     "Ket"],
    Ket[<|$CellContext`S[1, Q3`$] -> 0, $CellContext`S[2, Q3`$] -> 
      0, $CellContext`S[3, Q3`$] -> 0|>]], ",", 
   InterpretationBox[
    TemplateBox[{
      TemplateBox[{"\[VeryThinSpace]", "\"\[VeryThinSpace]\"", 
        SubscriptBox["1", 
         TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", 
           InterpretationBox[
            SubscriptBox["S", 
             TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", "1"}, "RowWithSeparators"]], 
            $CellContext`S[1, Q3`$]]}, "RowWithSeparators"]], 
        SubscriptBox["1", 
         TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", 
           InterpretationBox[
            SubscriptBox["S", 
             TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", "2"}, "RowWithSeparators"]], 
            $CellContext`S[2, Q3`$]]}, "RowWithSeparators"]], 
        SubscriptBox["1", 
         TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", 
           InterpretationBox[
            SubscriptBox["S", 
             TemplateBox[{",", "\",\"", "3"}, "RowWithSeparators"]], 
            $CellContext`S[3, Q3`$]]}, "RowWithSeparators"]]}, 
       "RowWithSeparators"]},
     "Ket"],
    Ket[<|$CellContext`S[1, Q3`$] -> 1, $CellContext`S[2, Q3`$] -> 
      1, $CellContext`S[3, Q3`$] -> 1|>]]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[14]=",
 CellID->1575726484,ExpressionUUID->"a8a0f61b-7f4b-44ba-a131-07ce0d5a6c3a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["Define the set of correctable errors.", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1757850539,ExpressionUUID->"6efecdef-3f02-431d-aef4-e669fe3db03d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"err", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Prepend", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"S", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"1", ",", "2", ",", "3"}], "}"}], ",", "1"}], "]"}], ",", 
     "1"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"err", "//", "PauliForm"}]}], "Input",
